This paper deals with the dualization of trellises, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses linear algebra techniques for dualization, which falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS). The use of characteristic generators is a common technique in coding theory, which is a subfield of information theory and falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the BCJR-construction, which is a technique used in communication networks (cs.NI). Finally, the paper discusses a conjecture formulated by Koetter/Vardy, which is related to machine learning and optimization (cs.LG).
